o smearing of this quantization.<br><br>The best data I have right now is from when I tanked Naggy for a while the other night (not on purpose, heh) and took a total of 5.5k damage. Any logs you have would be helpful. I'm hoping to get a few Avatar of War logs, because he has an obscene max, which would hopefully make the trend obvious (I'm not sure what trend, without data).<br><br>I wasn't able to find any other studies about the subject, so I assume no one has looked at it in depth.<br>- Joim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will KICK YOUR @$$</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 12:34:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1242.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ubermob tanking</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> different mobs with the same name can have different max hits<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Maybe common mobs, because level varies with each spawn but named raid-level mobs don't vary.  For example, Derakor the Vindicator will hit for 700 max every time you fight him.  There is the exception of the Dain though.<br><br>I may have missed something, but what exactly is the reason behind all this?  It's kind of futile to just get a bunch of logs and hope you see some kind of trend.  You ought to have a hypothesis of some kind, otherwise you're just making a large spreadsheet. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45589">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6